    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wide collars, usually on coats or day wear in the style of coats, that lie around the shoulders, often tapering to the waist, resembling a stole. For wider, capelike collars, use "berthas." For neck liners of ecclesiastical stoles, use "stole collars (liners)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
